@NODE M2-Install "Installing GUIEnvironment for M2Amiga"

Run the GE_M2Amiga-Install script to copy the interface modules into
your M2:Defs and M2:Mods drawers, to compile these modules and to copy
the examples into the M2:Examples drawer !

Don't forget to install the guienv.library and the geclass.library first !

@ENDNODE

@NODE M2-Interface "The M2Amiga interface module"

The M2Amiga interface modules contain all constants, structures and
functions explained in the documents. They are split in the common
way, so that you can use same as all other library modules of the
operating system.
Because M2Amiga can't currently call tag functions via the stack
all varargs stubs are missing.

The spelling of the constants is slightly different from the C decla-
ration:

- M2Amiga uses different prefixes without underscore. For example instead
  of GEG_VarAddress a gegVarAddress is used.

@ENDNODE

@NODE M2-Support "GUIEnvSupport for M2Amiga"

Appart from that the GUIEnvSupport module follows the same naming
conventions as explained in the chapter about the interface module !

@ENDNODE

